  "title": "Audit Associate",
  "description": "<p>• Execute audit procedures in compliance with professional standards</p>\n<p>• Identify significant accounting and auditing issues</p>\n<p>• Execute assigned audit tasks under supervision</p>\n<p>• Obtain audit evidence and document observations in audit work paper</p>\n<p>• Check financial statements to validate compliance with accounting standards</p>\n<p>• Communicate effectively and proactively to respond to clients and team members</p>\n<p>• Bachelor's or master’s degree in accountancy, or related qualification</p>\n<p>• Minimum 1 year of auditing or accounting experience preferred</p>\n<p>• Good time management and multi-tasking skills</p>\n<p>• Good English communication skills in writing and speaking</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em>Job Summary:</em></p>\n<p>CBD, Raffles Place, Audit, Tax, Accounting, inclusive, childcare friendly, elderly friendly, unlimited annual leaves, fintech, audit exposure, modern workplace and colleagues, good audit exposure in wide industries, good growth potential.</p>",
